t of RS-stereoisomers functions as a rational theoretical foundation for remedying conceptual faults and misleading terminology caused by conventional application of the theories of van’t Hoff and Le Bel.This book indicates that classic descriptions on organic and stereochemistry in textbooks should be thoroughly revised in conceptionally deeper levels. The proposed intermediate concept causes a paradigm shift leading to the reconstruction of modern stereochemistry on the basis of mathematical formulations. • Provides a new theoretical framework for the reorganization of mathematical stereochemistry. • Covers point-groups and permutation symmetry and exemplifies the concepts using organic molecules and inorganic complexes. • Theoretical foundations of modern stereochemistry for chemistry students and researchers, as well as mathematicians interested in chemical application of mathematics. Shinsaku Fujita has been Professor of Information Chemistry and Materials Technology at the Kyoto Institute of Technology from 1997-2007; before starting the Shonan Institute of Chemoinformatics and Mathematical Chemistry as a private laboratory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChemistryxMathematics. 0aStereochemistry. 4aEnantiomere. 4aOrganische Chemie. 4aStereochemie. 4aTheoretische Chemie. 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / Physical & Theoretical.2bisacsh  aComputational Chemistry.  aEnantiomers.  aOrganic Chemistry.  aStereochemistry.  aTheoretical Chemistry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry,  Materials Sc, Geosc 2015z9783110438789oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831103863700 cprintz